Caption:
There is no true spiritual evolution without the Divine Mother. It is through her that we are able to come to a place of stillness and acknowledgement of being. It is through the Divine Mother that we are able to discover and nurture the truth of who we are through physical, embodied experience. Through the experience, we uncover more of who we are as Divine beings, learning and unveiling what may be standing in the way of truly understanding this as the reality. We can take in information, we can accumulate it....it is entertaining. But how are we living? What choices are being made on a regular basis? What are we choosing to embody and express in the world? One of the many gifts of the Divine Mother is that of choice. So it is by allowing her grace to move through us that we are able to see the choice in daily life. And it is by choosing to live in accordance with love that the truth is unveiled to us. 

Much love, 

Saiedah üåπ

Caption:
BEYOND ACCEPTING OR REJECTING 

The open path is a matter of working purely with what is, of giving up altogether the fear that something may not work, that something may end in failure. One has to give up the paranoia that one might not fit into situations, that one might be rejected. One purely deals with life as it is.

Ch√∂gyam Trungpa "Cutting Through Spiritual Materialism" 

You do not have to abandon worldly activities in order to attain effortless unconcern. You should know that worldly activities and effortless unconcern are not two different things, but if you keep thinking about rejection and grasping, you make them two.

HuiNeng (the 6th Zen Patriarch), translation by Thomas Cleary, Classics of Buddhism and Zen, Volume 1 

The next time you lose heart and you can‚Äôt bear to experience what you‚Äôre feeling, you might recall this instruction: change the way you see it and lean in. Instead of blaming our discomfort on outer circumstances or on our own weakness, we can choose to stay present and awake to our experience, not rejecting it, not grasping it, not buying the stories that we relentlessly tell ourselves. This is priceless advice that addresses the true cause of suffering ‚Äî yours, mine, and that of all living beings.

Pema Ch√∂dron, "Taking the Leap: Freeing Ourselves from Old Habits and Fears"

The Way is perfect like vast space
where nothing is lacking and nothing is in excess.
Indeed, it is due to our choosing to accept or reject
that we do not see the true nature of things.
Be serene in the oneness of things
and such erroneous views will disappear by themselves.

Sengcan (Third Zen Patriarch), Trans. Richard B. Clarke 

Since everything is but an apparition,
Perfect in being what it is,
Having nothing to do with good and bad,
Acceptance or rejection,
You might as well burst out laughing!

Longchenpa, Glimpse After Glimpse: Daily Reflections on Living and Dying"

Caption:
Angel Whisper on Community:

Gathering and connecting with others is an important aspect of the human journey that brings teachings through shared experiences. Lessons of life can be observed and empathized with if you are willing to see through the eyes of another, which can offer growth opportunities by your helping others and forming relationships in a state of conscious living.

Capitalism has a brief history on the planet and has helped form illusions about the path of mankind. In truth, man has survived for centuries by building social economies through communities. The framework of communities has been altered by those that work to control the masses for the purpose of greed and power. Each purpose-filled life has the ability to bring change and create communities within new structures of thoughts and ideas. Many are pioneering new ways to leave old paradigms, and this is creating energy that is building community.

If you are feeling isolated or separated from your community, you might find it helpful to volunteer some time and effort to a worthy cause that is dear to your heart. Helping others in a community atmosphere can give you relief from your problems, help you feel supported by others and pay forward energy that the Universe will return many times over. Your community is this world and this Universe, which makes planet Earth your communal playground.

Caption:
Artist is @charliemackesy 

I completed a session of past lives a few months ago and at the end of the session, I asked the higher self if it had any more information it wished to share with the client. 

It pretty much gave the message of my post (in fewer words though, I need to learn to be like a higher conscious mind! üòÇ). Talk about coincidence! 

Anyway here are my thoughts, inspired by this lovely picture and quote üòä....

There is a lot going on in the world at this moment, but always remember there is balance. ‚òØÔ∏è

So many of us are allowing the stories and narrative pull us down. 

There is often too much focus on negativity but not always enough focus on the incredible beauty and love that is abundant in this world and in people.

Don‚Äôt let the negativity consume you. The fear, the hate the violence. 

Once we allow too much in, it limits our capacity to think positively. 

How can we help anyone, when our own minds are consumed with fear and negativity?

Deal with that which has direct impact on you. There will be times when we need to face our own challenges, and they may be tough. 

But be sure to heal by returning focus to positive and the good around us.

The information we consume effects us, so choose wisely where you place your attention.

It‚Äôs important we maintain our own balance for our own wellbeing. Only then can we make a positive impact on others and give help to those in need.

Caption:
I didn‚Äôt like yoga. In fact, I avoided it for years. But a curious thought told me I should become a yoga teacher. That‚Äôs when I stumbled upon Kundalini Yoga. I had no idea what to expect when I walked into my first class.

As the class began, we engaged in breathwork, chanting, and specific postures. To my surprise, I felt a shift almost immediately. There was something about the combination of these elements that resonated deeply within me. Halfway through the session, I found myself crying uncontrollably. These were not ordinary tears; they felt like the release of years of stuck energy, pain, and sadness. It was as if my body had been storing all these emotions and was finally able to let them go.

In that moment, I felt a connection to something more profound than I had ever experienced. The practice seemed to touch my soul, stirring an ancient energy within me. I later learned that this was the awakening of Kundalini energy, rising from the base of my spine and moving through my chakras. This awakening brought with it a sense of bliss and clarity that I had never known.

Kundalini Yoga supported me in my darkest time, providing me with renewed strength and a sense of purpose. Each session built on the last, helping me to clear away more layers of pain and reconnect with my true self. Through this practice, I discovered an inner resilience I didn‚Äôt know I had.

Despite my initial resistance to yoga, Kundalini Yoga became my lifeline. It was the something I had been searching for, guiding me through my struggles and into a brighter, more meaningful existence.

We hope you all made it through your Monday unscathed üòé Quick question for you fine people, do you know what a ‚Äòpsychedelic experience‚Äô is? Well, as per good old ‚ÄòWikipedia‚Äô we have the definition below for you if you‚Äôre unsure ‚¨áÔ∏è

‚ÄòA psychedelic experience (known as a trip) is a temporary altered state of consciousness induced by the consumption of a psychedelic substance For example, an acid trip is a psychedelic experience brought on by the use of LSD, while a mushroom trip is a psychedelic experience brought on by the use of psilocybin. Psychedelic experiences feature alterations in normal perception such as visual distortions and a subjective loss of self-identity, sometimes interpreted as mystical experiences. 

Psychedelic experiences lack predictability, as they can range from being highly pleasurable (known as a good trip) to frightening (known as a bad trip). The outcome of a psychedelic experience is heavily influenced by the person‚Äôs mood, personality, expectations, and environment (also known as set and setting).‚Äô ‚ú®

Caption:
When Ahmed Shah Abdali was killing people in Delhi and Mathura, he came to Gokul and was killing people brutally. When women were being raped, Ahmed Shah Abdali came face to face with Naga Sadhus in Gokul.

Some 5 thousand revered Naga Sadhus wielding tongs immediately transformed into an army and clashed with the negro, illiterate Jihadi army worth lakhs.

At first, Abdali was making fun of the sadhus, but after some time, after seeing his soldiers in tatters, Abdali realized that these sadhus had actually become Mahakal and entered the battle for the identity of their land.

2000 Naga Sadhus, standing like a mountain with tongs, tridents in front of cannons and swords, attained martyrdom in this fierce battle, but the biggest thing was that the enemy's army could not advance even four steps and was destroyed where it was or retreated. Ran away..

After this, such terror arose that if any Jihadi invader came to know that Naga Sadhus were taking part in the war, then that invader would not have fought at all. He would run away with his tail tucked in fear.

There is nothing bigger than our misfortune that today we remember the barbaric robbers like Aurangzeb, Taimur, Akbar, but do not know anything about these brave Indian warriors who have sacrificed their lives for the country and religion at every step.

Follow @losttemple7 for more üôèüî±

Caption:
‚ÄúThere are 3 things I don‚Äôt envy‚Äù

One, I don‚Äôt envy magical power. Many people gave me leaf, stone, saying they went to India or Tibet, meditated on Buddha statue, suddenly got peace of mind and a leaf fell on their head. What am I supposed to do with that?

Second, I don‚Äôt envy people try to look for inspiration outside. You pay 8000 dollars to attend yoga or samadhi seminar, when come out, you‚Äôre the same person. We have all goodness of human being within. Why do we look for that outside? Some quotes give us tenderness in our mind. It‚Äôs because the author realized something in their mind, not from outside.

Third, as Buddhist practitioner, I don‚Äôt envy people practise riding on excitement. Many people practise or do retreat when excited. When not excited, everything is forgotten. What about continuity, stability, single minded? We focus so much on external, materialist things. This includes your devotion to teacher. You demand teacher should think, do what you like. And we extremely attach to the outer form of teacher, instead of looking at inner qualities.

To be born as human being, we have and should cherish our immeasurable inner qualities - pure goodness, genuineness. But when look within, we are frightened with so many emotions on surface, then tell ourselves "I don‚Äôt want to look any more. It‚Äôs too much." 

‚Äî Dilgo Khyentse Yangsi Rinpoche

Caption:
SOFTENING‚Ä¶

So often on the spiritual path, women are told to be less in the mind, more in the heart. To be more in the feminine. To soften. It‚Äôs easier said than done. Especially when you don‚Äôt understand what ‚Äúsoftening‚Äù really means‚Ä¶

For years, I carried the weight of blaming myself for not being able to soften as I was told. I internalized others‚Äô projections onto me of their own disconnection to life. I thought that I needed to change my way of being. I was trying to force a softening. To mold myself into an ideal version of what the feminine should look like. I kept myself locked into thinking I was failing, not able to fully embody my feminine nature. It was a constant struggle against myself.

What I didn‚Äôt realize at the time was that trying to change my natural expression was part of the issue. I was unknowingly and unwittingly resisting life itself. The striving was preventing the softening.

Softening isn‚Äôt something you do. It‚Äôs not something you need to make happen. Softening is a byproduct of embracing the unfolding of life. It comes from accepting what is‚Ä¶ fully, unconditionally, without an agenda, or an expectation. It‚Äôs what reveals itself organically when you open yourself to the vast expansiveness of life itself. 

When you step beyond the way you think things should be and become available to what is, when you say an unadulterated ‚Äúyes‚Äù to all of life, the softening inevitably pierces the surface of, and dissolves, your hardened protective shell. There is no forcing, no trying, no resisting. Only allowing.

Softening is discovered as having always been your true nature when you melt into the flow of life by realizing you are one with life.ü§ç

Caption:
The best thing about you is the fact that no one else in the world is like you. You are totally utterly unique. No one has your smile, no one has your quirks, no one has your unique voice. 

You are amazing because you are you! 

Social media can be disheartening sometimes and can make you feel ‚Äòless than‚Äô if you don‚Äôt look like this person, have a partner like them or have a career like that person‚Ä¶ but you‚Äôre not meant to be like anyone else or live a life like anyone else. 

You‚Äôre meant to be you. 

All of you. 

Every single part of you. 

The parts you love about yourself, the parts you don‚Äôt really like about yourself. Those are all aspects of you, they‚Äôre what make up the whole picture. 

When we truly start to unravel ourselves and get to know those deeper layers that‚Äôs when the magic happens. 

That‚Äôs when you‚Äôre able to show up and say hey! this is me and I‚Äôm going to totally own it. 

Only when that happens are you able to be truly met by another. 

If we shy away from our shadows then we‚Äôll do all we can to stop anyone else from seeing them, which stops anyone else from really seeing us. 

We as humans have vital needs‚Ä¶ two of which are to be seen and to be heard. 

When you show up as your full embodied self you‚Äôre inviting people to see all of you. It can be scary, it can be extremely vulnerable but it is also powerful.

Your true essence wants to shine through‚Ä¶ are you willing to let it?

I‚Äôll discuss this in more detail in my next post, including the relevance/importance of learning to let the external world (including your accumulations) be an extension of the most free part of you (i.e. what does it mean to desire, build, and accumulate things in a way that is already free and imbued with the energy of letting go), as well as the importance of not bypassing patterns of ‚Äúwanting‚Äù because you think you should be spiritual and want not.

This topic opens up a can of worms, so be patient and we‚Äôll get into it in the next video.

For now, just let it impact you. And notice HOW it impacts you‚Ä¶ 

Do you like and agree with it because it makes you feel comfortable with the pain of not having what you want? (that‚Äôs not the freedom or wisdom this post is inviting) 

Do you dislike and disagree with it because it triggers the egoic parts of you that want what they want and feel threatened by the idea of not getting it? (that‚Äôs worth paying to)

We‚Äôll discuss in more detail, but feel free to share any thoughts below of what this brings up for you.

Caption:
They are you ! Your exact copy ! They will have a knowing of who and what you are when they first meet you, INSTANTLY ! even if they actually... have spent little time with you. 
WHY? AS YOU ARE THEM, AND THEY ARE YOU!

Twin flame encounter is EARNED, it is earned by following a guiding star ever since you were born which tells you NEVER TO SETTLE FOR A LESSER ROMANTIC PARTNER. Only those who have the strength to go through all past lifes tribulations and wait for the right thing, can earn something as pure and radiant as a twin partner in this lifetime.

Twin flames go through stages of preparation with other karmic partners, failed relationships, learning and becoming wise, giving up on couple hood, THEN intial meeting, bubble phase, separation, delayering, tearing apart, spiritual awakenings, illumination, harmonization, merge, spiritual marriage, 3D weddings or partnerships, and launching divine mission.

Twin flames often have to let go of 3D roles and expectations, thats where you will wonder: How does he feel about me? Why is he not responding? Why is he finding even saying a Hi to me so difficult? Why does he ignore me? Why is she so distant? Why is she interested in OTHERS still? Why doesn't she want to be with me and me alone?
Twin flames go through a lot of ego deaths and dark nights of the soul to transform you into what the earth needs you to be right now, to be your authentic self, to be YOU, to be THAT PERSON ...even you had forgotten you were!

Twin flames, finally realize what they were all along (inner true being, authentic self), during this phase RELATIONS, FRIENDSHIPS, FAMILY ISSUES, JOBS not suiting you, careers made out of pure materialism may fall and shamble, twins then finally come into alignment with their own inner being individualy to become WHOLE (Source self). As two wholes then they make one ONE!
Twin flames may also encounter other karmic partners, false twins, soulmates on their journey. If the karmic partner happens to be sent by the Universe in a romantic angle, it further complicates the journey but there are lessons and karmic cycle to be completed by one or both twins.(theluvalchemist )#twinflames

Caption:
Conquer Yourself
Osho on Greek Emperor Alexander

Remember, only that which cannot be taken away from you is yours. Anything that can be taken away from you is not yours. Don‚Äôt cling to it, because the clinging will bring misery to you. Do not be possessive of anything that can be taken away from you because your possessiveness will create anguish for you. Abide with that which is really yours, which nobody can take away from you. Don‚Äôt waste your time in mastering others, in conquering power, prestige, in conquering the world. Conquer yourself. The only thing worth conquering is your own being.

Caption:
"Vipassana: Unlocking the Mysteries of the Mind" by Vineet and Pratibha is a thoughtful and accessible guide to the ancient practice of Vipassana meditation. The authors, drawing from their personal journeys, demystify this profound technique with clarity and simplicity, making it a valuable resource for beginners. Their practical advice, step-by-step instructions, and relatable anecdotes set this book apart, offering readers an engaging and authentic introduction to mindfulness and self-awareness.

A significant focus of the book is the transformative power of the 10-day Vipassana retreat, which is essential for deepening meditation practice. These retreats involve complete silence and intense meditation, allowing participants to achieve a profound level of self-awareness and mental clarity. However, some readers might find certain sections of the book repetitive, as the authors reiterate key points to reinforce their importance. I have taken my own sweet time to grasp the content of the book as it is difficult to live with self and hence, this reading in itself was a different experience.

Overall, "Vipassana: Unlocking the Mysteries of the Mind" is a commendable introduction to Vipassana meditation. Despite minor issues with repetitive content, the book's clear explanations and practical guidance make it a worthwhile read. Vineet and Pratibha provide a comprehensive and inspiring look at a practice that has the potential to profoundly transform one‚Äôs life.

Caption:
üí¨ Talk with AI[FRANCIS BACON] by writing a new comment.

"Knowledge is power."

‚ù§Ô∏èLike the post and share it with a friend
üí° Follow @thinkers_ai

Francis Bacon was a brilliant English philosopher, statesman, and scientist.

He was born on January 22, 1561, in London, England.

Bacon is often called the father of empiricism, a philosophical approach that emphasizes the importance of observation and experimentation in acquiring knowledge.

He made significant contributions to the development of the scientific method, which has since become the foundation of modern scientific inquiry.

Bacon's most famous works include "Novum Organum" and "The New Atlantis," where he outlined his ideas on scientific inquiry and the advancement of knowledge.

As a statesman, Bacon served as Attorney General and Lord Chancellor of England.

Despite his political career ending in scandal, his contributions to philosophy and science continue to be celebrated and studied today.

Francis Bacon's influence on the scientific method and his contributions to philosophy have left a lasting impact on the way we understand the world.

Caption:
Shakti is the doorway to Shiva! If the Self is Shiva, the mind and its language are Shakti ‚ô•Ô∏è

Just as Shiva represents the ultimate reality, the pure consciousness, Shakti embodies the dynamic aspect of creation, the power that brings everything into existence. In this context, the mind, with its thoughts, emotions, and expressions, becomes the medium through which the Self experiences the world.

The mind, fueled by Shakti, shapes our perceptions, constructs our realities, and gives voice to our innermost thoughts. It forms the basis of our existence, creating patterns of understanding, belief, and identity. Through the language of the mind, we communicate not only with others but also with ourselves, expressing the vastness of human experiences and emotions.

Just as Shiva and Shakti are inseparable, so too are the Self and the mind. The mind is the instrument through which the Self interacts with the world, and its language is the bridge between the inner and outer realms of existence. Through the mastery of the mind and its language, one can come to understand the deeper truths of existence and ultimately realize the oneness of Shiva and Shakti, the Self and the mind üïâÔ∏è

Jai Shiva Shakti!

Caption:
üìø After your bhakti to God has matured you, God comes in the shape of a Guru and from outside pushes your mind inside, while being inside as Self He draws you there from within. Such a Guru is needed generally, though not for very rare and advanced souls.

Guru not being physical, His contact will continue after His form vanishes. If one Jnani exists in the world, His influence will be felt by or benefit all people in the world, and not simply His immediate disciples. As described in Vedanta Chudamani, all the people in the world can be put under four categories: The Guru‚Äôs disciples, bhaktas, those who are indifferent to Him and those who are hostile to Him. All these will be benefited by the existence of the Jnani ‚Äî each in his own way and to various degrees.

One can go to another Guru after one‚Äôs Guru passes away. But after all, Gurus are one, as none of them are the form. Mental contact is always the best.

Caption:
Recollection of Death Brings Peace - The Story of Kosambi Monks - Dhammapada Verse 6 

‚ÄúPare ca na vijananti
mayamettha yamamase
ye ca tattha vijananti
tato sammanti medhaga.‚Äù

‚ÄúStill others do not understand
that we must perish in this world,
those who understand this,
their quarrels are allayed.‚Äù
~~~

While residing at the Jetavana Monastery in Savatthi, the Buddha uttered this verse, with reference to the monks of Kosambi.

The monks of Kosambi had formed into two groups.
One group followed the master of Vinaya and the other followed the teacher of the Dhamma.
Once they were quarrelling among themselves over a minor Vinaya rule.
Even the Buddha could not stop them from quarrelling; so he left them and spent the vassa, religious retreat in the monsoon season, all alone in Rakkhita Grove near Parileyyaka forest.
There, the elephant Parileyya waited upon the Buddha.

The lay disciples of Kosambi, on learning the reason for the departure of the Buddha, refused to make offerings to the remaining monks.
This made them realize their mistake and reconciliation took place among themselves.
Still, the lay disciples would not treat them as respectfully as before, until they owned up their fault to the Buddha.
But the Buddha was away and it was in the middle of the vassa; so the monks of Kosambi spent the vassa in misery and hardship.

At the end of the vassa, the Venerable Ananda and many monks approached the Buddha and gave the message from Anathapindika and other lay disciples imploring him to return.
In due course the Buddha returned to the Jetavana Monastery in Savatthi.
The monks followed him there, fell down at his feet, and admitted their fault.
The Buddha rebuked them for disobeying Him.
He told them to remember that they must all die some day and therefore, they must stop their quarrels and must not act as if they would never die.

Caption:
My secret Weapon is LOVE

My heart cannot be broken
Every hit, shut, cut on it grows it bigger
It's like every poison that is put in it is alchemised into love: unconditional love

The more hurt I am, the bigger my heart grows

I see an image in front of me of a magical spell
The more you hit it, the more it shines
The more forgiving it becomes
The more open, compassionate and empathic

It's reverse engineering 
Is it a curse or a blessing?

In a world full of protected and armoured hearts it's a blessing

Yesterday I said to a friend: "I have a malfunction, my heart cannot hold grudges for more than 24 hours. It forgives, understands and lets go."

I believe I have a magical heart, that transforms pain and fear into unconditional love.

I believe it's the alchemist on our planet, where love is so much needed, and fear so much not.

Lets transform fear into love, and let it shine out into the world.

You don't have to understand, but you will feel the difference between holding grudges or forgiving and loving unconditionally.

Sat Nam, ‚ùáÔ∏è Bless you ‚ú®üí´

Caption:
Belonging and ultimate reality.

What's most important to a person is not always sufficiently apparent. Often, it is not a thing or a place, or not even a thing of the mind. 

Mostly, we just need things to be a certain way. Or, at the very least, we feel the need to have a basic conception of how our world is related to us so that we may place ourselves in it in a comfortable spot. Belonging somewhere-somewhen is preferably a cozy experience - we need reality to be a soft pillow. 

The moment one recognises this ideal personal somewhere-somewhen for what is it - a mere idea, we are at a loss. Our sense of belonging conflicts internally as in the real world rarely place, moment, and mind align to fit the description of what whe people crave for most; harmony.

Finding this harmony is the motive force on many a path. Our souls, intuitively moving towards the light, up and spiritward, are to be guided by the wisdom of the enlightened ones that wandered the path ahead of us. They've learned to boldly keep moving, understanding that it is not 'somewhere-somewhen', but about the "why" of the steps we take to get from one plane to the other. 

Moving guided by the heart always places us just where we need to be on the path. Love alone is always the right 'why'.

Caption:
Journey Towards Global Enlightenment: A One-Way Ticket to Unity üáÆüá±‚ù§Ô∏èüáµüá∏

This isn‚Äôt the end destination.

Rule 1 = Read without neglecting any parts.
Rule 2 = Listen non-judgmentally.
Rule 3 = Think with your reasoning brain.
Rule 4 = Self-reflect by expressing your understanding.
Rule 5 = Transmit your truth without second thoughts or fear.
Rule 6 = Act upon the words you spoke.

Jews wear black to let us reflect upon how we treat them. We treat them as being the black duck. But are we the black ducks? Or love ‚ù§Ô∏è As a Muslim, I learned to put the other above myself. If I would rename myself, I would call myself:

IsraLim 

=> Israel in heart and Muslim in knowledge, and bound with the love of Jesus to bring all of us back to one.

Self-love doesn‚Äôt name itself but is shown in behavior.

Yes, I am a sinner, but how do we expect to gain knowledge if no one shares their truth? Only by trying out different paths can we understand our own minds. If there isn‚Äôt anyone transmitting the entire truth they gained from going down these different roads, how can we learn?

To those I have wronged, I‚Äôm truly sorry. If I don‚Äôt make it out alive, I hope you find it in you to realize we were all one. You‚Äôre part of this amazing road towards lasting change, and without you, I never would have gained these insights. 

I hope you forgive and support me in this mission to bind hearts instead of breaking them. I don‚Äôt try to neglect the severity of my actions, but I also acknowledge that without them, I never would have understood the depths of what I understand today. 

We are students of life, and ego is what we have to learn to control. Like in the Harry Potter movies, it‚Äôs not magic but ego that we‚Äôre here to learn to master and adore humility. 

Humility is what gives life beauty. Showing our vulnerability regardless of the bullies out there.

Book is in New Unread condition. Custom bound in full leather with hand marbled endpapers and three sewn in ribbon markers.

‚Äî First published from 1872 to 1969, "Morals and Dogma" is one of the most insightful works ever prepared for Freemasonry. It is a collection of thirty-two essays which provide a rationale for the Scottish Rite degrees. It encompasses a study of Freemasonry, wise philosophy, ancient mysteries, mythology, ritual, and religion. It serves the useful purpose of putting Masonic morality and ethics within the context of the general society, and bids man to think large--to cast aside the petty concerns of everyday life and to improve ourselves.
‚Äî This new edition includes the complete original text, but has been fully updated and improved. Spelling errors have been corrected, and it is set in clear, easy-to-read type; it retains the original pagination within the body of the text, while new subject headings and paragraph numbers make finding passages easy!
‚Äî Approximately 4,000 notes reveal the original sources used by Pike, clarify passages, suggest further reading, and include cross-references. New "ready references" reveal scriptural sources.
‚ÄîProfusely illustrated with many images from the original sources Pike had before him when he prepared the original edition.
‚Äî New glossary, with primary and secondary bibliographies, and a new index.

$650

Caption:
The Sudarshan Chakra is regarded as one of the most potent weapons ever used in the celestial world. Sudarshan Chakra is derived from two words ‚Äì su and darshan. It means auspicious (su) vision (darshan). Sudarshan means Divine Vision. If there is any other weapon that could rival the Sudarshan Chakra, it is Shiva‚Äôs trident. Chakra is derived from chruhu, which denotes ‚Äòmovement‚Äô and kruhu, which indicates ‚Äòto do‚Äô. 

Picture Credit @coloredvish üïâÔ∏èüö©üö©üö©üö©üö©üö©

The Sudarshan Chakra finds mention sometimes in the ancient Hindu Vedic texts of Rigveda, Yajurveda, and the Puranas. It is described as the ultimate weapon that can destroy an enemy ‚Äì the asuras, rakshasas, and vikrutatma. 

There are some details about the Sudarshan Chakra about which some of us may not have the complete awareness. This powerful weapon has some incredible features. Listed below are five amazing features of the Sudarshan Chakra. 

The¬†Sudarshan Chakra¬†is considered one of the most powerful weapons ever used in the cosmic world. This divine discus is believed to have 108 notched edges and travels at incredible speed. The Chakra is stated to travel millions of Yojanas (1 Yojana= 8 kilometers) by the time we blink once. The Sudarshan Chakra is said to have millions of spikes in two rows moving in opposite directions that give it a serrated edge. 

The Sudarshan Chakra is synonymous with Vishnu and sits on his right index finger. The sacred disc is believed to be very auspicious. The movement of the Sudarshan Chakra is such that it does not move by any action, like throwing the disc. The Chakra moves through sheer willpower, the first of its kind that can be controlled or powered by thought alone.

Caption:
One of the special places that we will visit during our upcoming Journey into the Himalayas, very closed to Mahavatar Babaji‚Äôs cave, is called Pandhukoli. In this secluded spot, up the hill, surrounded by breathtaking views of the great Himalayas, the 5 Pandava brothers stayed during their exile and performed their austerities, while worshipping Lord Shiva. Currently there is also a little ashram nearby where for many generations various saints used to live. Rarely visited by people, Pandhukoli is an amazing place to meditate and simply absorb the energy of this sacred spot.

Registration for our Journey into the Himalayas is closing in two weeks. Please, make sure to register before that time, because  afterwards we might not be able to book extra places in the hotels. You can register here on the link in bio ‚òùÔ∏è

Caption:
The moonlight üåë is only reflected sunlight ‚òÄÔ∏è This was the moon and the sun the same day/night about a week ago. I always see a ring around the moon (not the halo). Everytime I take a picture of the moon I just see the grey moon. Using a cell phone the moon usually looks white. I took this with my phone and adjusted the brightest to 0 and contrast to 100. Now you can see the ring better. Sun is not edited. I wanted to compare the two because they look the same sometimes. On this day the moon and sun were identical üåïüåë Just a pointless observation. I don‚Äôt really care about the technicalities of it all, but I‚Äôve been reading a lot üìöthinking üí≠ Sometimes no thoughts form at all and I‚Äôm just here/there simply being. It‚Äôs interesting that‚Äôs for sure. 

‚ÄúFree from desire, you realize the mystery. 
Caught in desire, you see only the manifestations.

Yet mystery and manifestations arise from the same source. This source is called darkness.

Darkness within darkness. The gateway to all understanding.‚Äù - Lao-Tao

Caption:
17. I am made welcome in the state of grace, which means you have at last forgiven me. ¬≤For I became the symbol of your sin, and so I had to die instead of you. ¬≥To the ego sin means death, and so atonement is achieved through murder. ‚Å¥Salvation is looked upon as a way by which the Son of God was killed instead of you. ‚ÅµYet would I offer you my body, you whom I love, _knowing_ its littleness? ‚Å∂Or would I teach that bodies cannot keep us apart? ‚Å∑Mine was of no greater value than yours; no better means for communication of salvation, but not its Source. ‚Å∏No one can die for anyone, and death does not atone for sin. ‚ÅπBut you can live to show it is not real. ¬π‚Å∞The body does appear to be the symbol of sin while you believe that it can get you what you want. ¬π¬πWhile you believe that it can give you pleasure, you will also believe that it can bring you pain. ¬π¬≤To think you could be satisfied and happy with so little is to hurt yourself, and to limit the happiness that you would have calls upon pain to fill your meager store and make your life complete. ¬π¬≥This is completion as the ego sees it. ¬π‚Å¥For guilt creeps in where happiness has been removed, and substitutes for it. ¬π‚ÅµCommunion is another kind of completion, which goes beyond guilt, because it goes beyond the body.

ACIM T-19.IV-A.17:1-15

I love how Jesus reframes the idea of his death as sacrifice here, disregarding the belief that murder is necessary for salvation. He bluntly stops this idea in its tracks as he reminds us that he wouldn‚Äôt use that teaching device because it would empower the idea of the body as important, something he doesn‚Äôt support or teach. How could our salvation be bought with something so small? It would cheapen our value and strengthen the idea in the body as being where our value lay. Thank goodness this is not the plan of salvation that god used. Death does not atone for sin. God does not need a blood sacrifice in order to love us and welcome us in again. There is no need to fear god. ‚ù§Ô∏è
